3B. (1) For the purpose of furthering the overriding objective referred to in section 3A, the Court shall handle all matters presented before it for the purpose of attaining the following aims -
(a) the just determination of the proceedings;
(b) the efficient use of available judicial and administrative resources;
(c) the timely dispose; of the proceeding, and all other proceedings in the court, at a cost affordable by the respective parties; and
(d) the use of suitable technology.
